The article is a memorandum addressed to the Secretary of Defense regarding the Presidential Waiver of Statutory Requirements Pursuant to Section 303 of the Defense Production Act of 1950. The memorandum states that the President determines the need to increase the production capacity of material critical for defense against adversarial aggression, and that a shortfall in this area would severely impair national defense capability. As a result, the President waives certain requirements of the Act to expand and accelerate domestic production capability of critical weapons and equipment needed for national defense. The memorandum concludes by authorizing and directing the publication of the memorandum in the Federal Register. The memorandum is signed by Joseph R. Biden Jr., the President of the United States.